      <section id="getting-started">
        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <p>Thank you for choosing BidMart as your online bidding platform. This Help Center is designed to provide you with the information you need to get started using our service.</p>
        <h3>Create an Account</h3>
        <p>To use BidMart, you will need to create an account. You can do this by clicking the "Register" button in the top right corner of the homepage. Follow the prompts to enter your personal information and create a password. Once you have created an account, you will be able to start bidding on auctions.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="Buying">
        <h3>Buying on BidMart</h3>
        <p>Here are some tips for buying items on BidMart:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Set a budget for the item you want to buy.</li>
          <li>Read the item description carefully before placing a bid.</li>
          <li>Check the seller's feedback rating to ensure they are a reputable seller.</li>
          <li>Be prepared to pay for the item if you win the auction.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Selling on BidMart</h3>
        <p>Here are some tips for selling items on BidMart:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Write a detailed item description and include clear photos of the item.</li>
          <li>Set a price for your item</li>
          <li>Monitor the bids placed on your item</li>
      </section>

      <section id="bidding">
        <h3>Bidding</h3>
        <p>To place a bid on an item in an auction, simply click the on the item you want to bid for. Enter the amount you want to bid and click "Place bid". Please note that bids are binding, so make sure you are willing to pay the amount you bid before submitting.</p>
        <h5>Outbidding and Maximum Bids</h5>
        <p>If someone else places a bid on the same item, you will be notified via email.</p>
        <h5>Auto Bidding</h5>
        <p>Currently, BidMart does not offer auto bidding functionality. However, we are always working to improve our platform and may add this feature in the future.</p>
        <p>Here you can learn about bidding on auctions.</p>
        <p>When you find an item you want to bid on, click the item and then scroll down to the auction information section and enter your bid amount. You will be prompted to confirm your bid before it is submitted. If someone outbids you, you will receive a notification via email</p>
        <p>Please note that bids cannot be retracted, so make sure to bid carefully and only bid what you can afford. If you are the highest bidder when the auction ends, you will be notified by email.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions about bidding or need assistance with placing a bid, please contact our customer support team.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="payments">
        <h3>Payments</h3>
        <p>At the moment, BidMart does not have a payment system in place. When you win an auction, you will be notified by email. In this email, you will receive the seller's contact information and you can contact them directly to arrange for payment and delivery of your item.</p>
        <p>It's important to note that the seller may have their own preferred payment method, so it's important to discuss this with them. We recommend using a secure payment method to protect yourself from fraud.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about the payment process, please feel free to <a class="text-decoration-none" href="#contact">contact us</a> and we will be happy to assist you.</p>
